# Next.js 15 Development Patterns

## App Router Structure
- Use the App Router in [src/app/](mdc:frontend/src/app/)
- Implement proper file-based routing
- Use `layout.tsx` for shared layouts
- Use `page.tsx` for page components
- Use `loading.tsx` for loading states
- Use `error.tsx` for error boundaries

## Server Components
- Use React Server Components by default
- Implement proper data fetching in Server Components
- Use `use client` directive only when necessary
- Leverage Server Components for SEO and performance

## API Routes
- Implement API routes in [src/app/api/](mdc:frontend/src/app/api/)
- Use proper HTTP methods and status codes
- Implement proper error handling
- Use Zod for request/response validation
- Return proper JSON responses

## Metadata and SEO
- Implement metadata in layout files
- Use dynamic metadata for dynamic routes
- Implement proper Open Graph tags
- Use structured data for better SEO
- Implement proper canonical URLs

## Performance Optimization
- Use Next.js Image component for images
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use dynamic imports for code splitting
- Implement proper loading states
- Use React Suspense for async components

## Environment Configuration
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Implement proper environment validation
- Use Next.js built-in environment support
- Follow security best practices for secrets

## Error Handling
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use Next.js error handling patterns
- Implement proper logging
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Handle network errors gracefully
